 1069
Your Honor,

I stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of assault. I admit that I pushed my employee to the ground and kicked him in the stomach. This incident occurred in a fit of extreme anger, resulting from his serious mistake at work, which would have financially impacted my company. 

I acknowledge the gravity of my actions and the harm I caused to the victim. Immediately after the incident, I deeply regretted my actions and took responsibility by bringing him to the nearest emergency room to ensure his well-being. I want to emphasize that I have already offered to pay for the remaining hospital bills, as a token of my sincere remorse.

In mitigation of my guilt, I would like to bring attention to my personal circumstances. At the age of 40, I have maintained a clean record, and this regretful incident is an isolated occurrence. I humbly request that my previous clean record be considered as a mitigating factor in determining an appropriate sentence for my actions.

I also wish to express my commitment to ensuring such an incident is never repeated. In light of this, I have taken proactive steps to address my impulsive reactions. I have sought counseling and have demonstrated a sincere willingness to learn healthier methods of managing my anger. I firmly believe that by doing so, I can prevent similar incidents from happening in the future.

Furthermore, I would like to address the honorable court and express my deepest apologies to the victim and their family. I am fully aware of the pain and distress I have caused them, and I can assure you that my remorse is genuine. I am wholeheartedly committed to making amends and rectifying the harm I have done.

Finally, I kindly ask the court to consider any additional mitigating factors that may warrant a more lenient sentence. While it does not justify my actions, the intense provocation caused by the significant financial consequences of my employee's mistake should be taken into consideration.

In conclusion, I acknowledge my guilt and plead for your consideration of the mitigating factors presented. I am committed to learning from this experience, making amends, and becoming a contributing member of society once again.

Thank you for your attention.

